bib_record.title: Gamma radiation from the alpha particle bombardment of C-12.

free_txt: The ONR-CIT tandem accelerator.
A 10.2*10.2 cm NaI(Tl) crystal which was
adjustable in radius and angle (in one plane) about the
target. Most of the data were taken with a 30.5 cm
diameter cylindrical lead shield around the crystal;
however, where angles greater than 90 degr. were
involved this lead shield was removed and the bare
crystal used. Removing the cylindrical shield resulted
in a 55% increase in room background in the energy
region of interest to his experiment. Beam deposition
of natural carbon on the targets was minimized by the
use of an in-line liquid nitrogen cold trap and ion
pumping at the target chamber.
Energy error
The ONR-CIT tandem accelerator.
The data have been corrected for dead time losses
(always under 7%) and time dependent room background.
Data represent the number of pulses per microcoulomb
of He+ ions observed within a window corresponding to
gamma ray energies from 0.8 Ex to 1.1 Ex, where Ex is
the appropriate excitation energy in 16O determined
from the bombarding energy Ea by using the relation
The NaI(Tl) crystal was set at 45 degr. to the beam
axis with its face approximately 2 cm from the target
spot.
